The number of confirmed Coronavirus cases in Africa on Friday reached 3,937,028. The Africa Centres for Disease Control and Prevention (Africa CDC) made this known in a tweet via its Twitter account. The Africa CDC said the death toll related to the pandemic stood at 105,001, while 3,512,473 patients across the continent had recovered from the disease. It also stated the affected countries in terms of the number of confirmed positive cases are South Africa, Morocco, Tunisia, Egypt, and Ethiopia, the agency noted. “South Africa has lost 50,462 lives to the virus which makes it the most affected amongst other African countries. “Egypt stands in as the second most affected country at 10,871, and Morocco, at 8,669,” the tweet said.